<FILEID>AP-NR-10-13-89 1227EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>d p AM-BRF--CandidateDeath     10-13 0102</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Candidate Death,0105</SECOND>
<HEAD>Candidate Dies While Stumping</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROSENDALE, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A candidate for town justice suffered a
fatal heart attack while addressing a women's club during a ``meet
the candidates'' session.
   Barbara Heleen, 50, a Democrat, suffered the heart attack
Thursday night while addressing the Women's Club of Rosendale at
the Williams Lake Hotel, authorities said.
   ``We're all in shock right now,'' said town Supervisor Beatrice
Havranek, who was at the meeting. ``She just collapsed and that's
all that happened; she collapsed and that was it.''
   People in the audience tried to revive the candidate, and
paramedics made additional attempts.
</TEXT>
