<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through a shantytown Friday,
killing eight people, destroying 200 houses and leaving 1,000
people homeless, officials said. Authorities blamed arsonists.
   The dead were trapped in the mud-and-straw houses when the fire
engulfed the Kallayanpur slums on the northern outskirts of the
