<FIRST>r a AM-MarketDrop-Percentages 1stLd-Writethru a0728 10-13 0233</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Market Drop-Percentages, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0728,0244</SECOND>
<HEAD>Biggest Daily Percentage Losses for Dow Industrials</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 3rd graf from bottom to CORRECT year of Jan. 8 drop to
1988, sted 1987. A version also moved on the financial wire. With AM-Market
Drop.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Dow Jones industrial average's percentage
fall Friday was the 12th worst since the average was increased to
30 stocks on Oct. 1, 1928. Here are the 15 worst days for the
average, including the point change.
   Oct. 19, 1987 _ 22.6 percent, off 508.00 to 1,738.74.
   Oct. 28, 1929 _ 12.8 percent, off 38.33 to 260.64.
   Oct. 29, 1929 _ 11.7 percent, off 30.57 to 230.07.
   Nov. 6, 1929 _ 9.9 percent, off 25.55 to 232.13.
   Aug. 12, 1932 _ 8.4 percent, off 5.79 to 63.11.
   Oct. 26, 1987 _ 8.0 percent, off 156.83 to 1,793.93.
   July 21, 1933 _ 7.84 percent, off 7.55 to 88.71.
   Oct. 18, 1937 _ 7.75 percent, off 10.57 to 125.74.
   Oct. 5, 1932 _ 7.15 percent, off 5.09 to 66.07.
   Sept. 24, 1931 _ 7.07 percent, off 8.20 to 107.79.
   July 20, 1933 _ 7.07 percent, off 7.32 to 96.26.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>Oct. 13, 1989 _ 6.91 percent, off 190.58 to 2,569.26.</NOTE>
<TEXT>
