<HEAD>Ford Says It Has Acquired 5 Percent of Jaguar</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. has boosted its ownership
share of Jaguar PLC to 5 percent on its way to acquiring 15 percent
of the British luxury carmaker, the No. 2 U.S. automaker said
Friday.
   The Federal Trade Commission said last week it would have no
objection to Ford acquiring 15 percent of Jaguar, the maximum
allowed by the end of 1990, according to Jaguar by-laws.
   Jaguar has said Ford's move is unwelcome. General Motors Corp.
and Jaguar have said they were involved in discussions that could
result in GM holding a stake in Jaguar.
   Ford held 1 percent of Jaguar stock before its announcement last
month of its intentions to acquire the 15-percent share of Jaguar.
