<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Petroleum futures prices finished mixed Friday,
with wholesale home heating oil retreating after a rally the
previous session.
   Crude oil and gasoline futures gained.
   The contract for November delivery of No.2 heating oil pulled
back by 0.30 cent to 60.87 cents a gallon on the New York
Mercantile Exchange, erasing a portion of Thursday's 1.36-cents
surge. Other contract months also declined.
   Among other refined petroleum products traded on the New York
Merc, the November contract for wholesale unleaded gasoline went up
0.58 cent to 56.15 cents a gallon, more than making up for
Thursday's drop of 0.16 cent. Contracts for later delivery also
settled higher.
   The November contract for West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark
grade of U.S. crude oil, added 42 cents to settle at $20.89 per
42-gallon barrel after rising 22 cents on Thursday. Contracts
calling for delivery December through February sported more modest
gains.
