<FIRST>u f AM-MagazineDeal     10-13 0211</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Magazine Deal,0221</SECOND>
<HEAD>Lang Completes Deal for Ms., Sassy Magazines; Plans to Publish Ad-Free
Ms.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Magazine investor Dale W. Lang said Friday he
had completed his previously-disclosed plans to acquire control of
Ms. and Sassy magazines, and said he plans to begin publishing Ms.
without advertising.
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed, but officials familiar
with the transaction said it gives Lang a 70 percent interest in
Matilda Publications, the company that has run both magazines for
the past year.
   The remaining 30 percent interest is held by Citicorp Venture
Capital Partners.
   Ms., which has been an advocate for women's causes, has not been
profitable in its 17 years of publication and has often been at
odds with advertisers, Lang said.
   ``We understand the advertising community's difficulty with
buying advertising in an advocacy magazine, but it's a major
problem in growing the magazine to profitability,'' he said.
   ``In order to serve the reader, Ms. must be published without
external pressures,'' he said, explaining the decision to quit
taking advertising.
   Ms. is currently a monthly magazine with a circulation of
550,000.
   Sassy, launched in March 1988 with a rate base of 250,000, has
grown since to a circulation of 450,000. It is aimed at teenage
girls.
</TEXT>
